DefaultMessage.SourceString: It's very interesting... <b>once you understand it. </>

Message.SourceString: Did... did I go to <b>The Spire?</>

But... I found <b>the Artifact! </>
I shouldn't be here...
I think I've made a <b>huge mistake.</>

DefaultMessage.SourceString: My work cannot be rushed, and the <b>Old Guardians</> must have their dues.
My work cannot be rushed, and the <b>Old Guardians</> must have their dues.
I need more time. Come back later.
Patience.
Interesting message, no?
It will take some time.
May the <b>Old Guardians</> guide you home again.
There is old magic in <enemy>the Spire</>. Be cautious in your explorations.
Return to me when you have gathered what you need from the<b> Crystal Shards. </>
And I will require a few favors in return.
This is proving more <b>difficult</> than I had hoped.
I need more time.
Now leave me alone. I have work to do.
Listen first. Talk later.
Thief? Occasionally. But this time I had something else in mind.
This message of yours is directing you to <b>the Spire. </>
I have been working on a way to disguise myself to finally enter the <b>Spire's inner sanctum. </>
If you'd like I could decode this little message of yours.
Coincidentally, this is a place of great interest to me.
A talisman looted from a <enemy>Spire Guardian's body...</>
And a sacrifice from the wilds in the form of a <b>Wolf Fang, a Boar Tusk, and three Chicken Feathers. </>
That <b>device</> of yours is waiting for you nearby.
Bring me this and the <b>Old Guardians</> may just bless our endeavors.
My work cannot be rushed, and the <b>Old Guardians</> must have their dues.
Bring me an <b>artifact stolen</>from the Spire, a Spire <enemy>Talisman looted</> from a Spire Guardian's body...
A Wolf Fang, Boar Tusk, and three Chicken Feathers.
And then leave me to my work.
Do not rush the <b>Old Guardians. </>
The <b>Old Guardians</> smile upon our efforts.
Your disguise is waiting for you near <enemy>the Spire. </>
They will work their magic when they see fit.
Among your things you will find a <b>Crystal Focus</> pickaxe.
Bring me an artifact <b>stolen</> from the Spire. Mind you, it <b>must</> be stolen.
The deed is not done.
I can make a disguise for you as well... if you bring me what I require.
Sample the Crystal Shards and <b>return the device</> to me.
May the <b>Old Guardians</> guide your path.
Something's wrong... isn't it?
